      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (NIH) is the clinically relevant hemolysis metric mandated by FDA guidance. Secondary QoIs (wall shear stress, exposure time distributions) are directly linked to the hemolysis power-law model. All QoIs map directly to the COU decision criterion.",
