      "rationale": "All model inputs (geometry, fluid properties, operating conditions, hemolysis model constants) are documented with sources and uncertainty bounds. Monte Carlo sampling (N=1000) propagates input uncertainty through to NIH predictions. 95th-percentile NIH remains below clinical threshold.",
